author: Reuters
title: Wet markets in China's Wuhan struggle to survive coronavirus blow
description: Fish and vegetable merchants are reopening stalls at wet markets in China's central city of Wuhan as it lifts a months-long lockdown against the coronavirus pandemic, but their future looks uncertain with few customers as the virus stigma persists.
